  <original-body>Currently the rake:db_create and rake:db_drop tasks will connect to the PostgreSQL server with a nil database, which causes PostgreSQL to look for a database with the same name as the connecting user.  This isn't really feasible as the database is not guaranteed to exist. 

PostgreSQL always has a template1 database - let's connect to it when creating/dropping other databases.

Patch: http://github.com/pdeffendol/rails/commit/bf10dfda19c543db6de5b690a7ea1d7cd5359e6a</original-body>
